
[1]shrove-tuesday

   SHROVE-TUESDAY, Tuesday.] Confession-time; confession-Teusday; the
   Tuesday after Quinquagesima Sunday; or the day immediately preceding
   the first of Lent, or Ash Wednesday; on which day, all the people of
   England when of the Catholic religion, were obliged to confess their
   sins one by one to their parish priests; after which they dined on
   pancakes or fritters. The latter ppractice still continues. The bell
   rung on this day is called pancake-bell.
